<div class="center">
'''Level 448''' is the 449<sup>th</sup> level in the Backrooms.
==Description==
{{Blurimage|file=Hideandseek1.jpg|caption=The infamous image of Level 448.|hovertext=Hide now, before you lose.}}
'''Level 448''' is an average American house which is complete with a liminal feel, similar to [[Level 53]]. Although '''Level 448'''’s exterior is not typically accessible, a large suburban neighborhood expands beyond the confines of '''Level 448'''’s house. The houses look old and deserted, with neglected yards and trees that seem oddly twisted. During the day, the place seems gray and gloomy, as if it was stuck at night-time. Wanderers say they've seen semi-transparent figures peeking out from inside the empty houses.  

'''Level 448'''’s layout is composed of places normally found within suburban houses, like a living room, bedrooms, and a kitchen. The house contains furniture, reminiscent of the glary styles found in a '90s house, although many others, including broken furniture, have already been confirmed to exist here. The wall of this level hides blood and torn wallpaper, bearing witness to marks of violence and the passage of time, with evident signs of wear and tear. Broken glass shards scattered across the floor, adding to the atmosphere of this forsaken space, leading the wanderer to sanity loss. The very architecture of '''Level 448''' seems to conspire against wanderers as well, with doors leading to nowhere and staircases that loop endlessly, trapping the unwary in a nightmarish maze, therefore, being non-Euclidean. The furniture, although reminiscent of '90s styles, occasionally takes on a surreal quality.
{{Blurimage|file=448-2.jpg|caption=A version of a kitchen of the level.|hovertext=There's no hiding here.}}
When one enters '''Level 448''', everything seems normal at first. But then, an ominous, childlike voice begins to count down from 30. At this point, you have only 30 seconds to choose a hiding spot. Eventually, when the 30 seconds are up, the voice will say, “Ready or not, here I come”. At that moment, a very hostile entity resembling a child faceling will spawn and begin to hunt wanderers down. If a wanderer ends up being found by the entity, it will proceed to kill the one who was found, usually by crushing their spine and ribcage by wrapping its arms around the back of the subject. Other methods have been observed, including hitting the subject's head against a blunt object or even dismembering them.

Surviving is difficult, if one wants to join the challenge, albeit impossible to not, wanderers must always be on the move and always be quiet, as the chances of being found increase by 10% every minute they are hidden. The entity’s speed and stamina also increase every minute a wanderer is hidden. This game of cat and mouse will continue until they perish or exit '''Level 448'''. If a wanderer enters with a group, the entity will usually look for individual members of the group if they split up and will not stop until all of them perish or all the survivors exit '''Level 448'''.

Each encounter with the childlike being brings not only the threat of physical harm but also the potential for psychological trauma, as the entity seems to draw on the deepest fears and anxieties of those, it pursues before killing the wanderer. Whispers echoing through the walls suggest that the entity is not the only danger here, adding psychological torment. It's important to note that wanderers have speculated that the shadow-like creature peeking out the empty houses was, indeed, the childlike entity. Consequently, this theory affirms that those houses are houses that wanderers are in. Although it might be true, trying to help is currently futile, given that they can't leave the suburban house.

